The PDF/A standard defines provisions for long term archiving of electronic documents in the PDF format. All content in a PDF/A file must be contained in such a way that viewing or printing of the file can be achieved reliably over a long period of time.

The PDF/E standard defines provisions for the use and exchange of engineering documents in the PDF format. The PDF/X standard defines provisions for reliable PDF exchange in the graphic arts industry. PDF/X files must contain all page content and resources for predictable viewing and ouput.
